prime_award_base_transaction_description: TORFP 2332 LOW-DENSITY UAS-OPERATION COMMUNICATION EVALUATION (LUCE)
subawardee_business_types: SELF CERTIFIED SMALL DISADVANTAGED BUSINESS,FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,BUSINESS OR ORGANIZATION,LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY
subaward_description:
"THE SCOPE OF THIS PROJECT INCLUDES SIMULATION AND MODELING ANALYSIS ALONG WITH LIVE FLIGHT EVALUATIONS CENTERING ON OPERATIONAL IMPLICATIONS AND POTENTIAL REQUIREMENTS ASSOCIATED WITH COMMUNICATIONS. THE SPECIFIC FOCUS BEING ON THE CURRENT NAS, DIRECT PILOT-CONTROLLER REQUIREMENT OF 250MS-300MS. SOME OF THE RESEARCH AREAS INCLUDE:
• COMMUNICATION REQUIREMENTS VIABLE/FEASIBLE FOR REMOTELY PILOTED VEHICLES OPERATING IN THE NAS.
• CURRENT (OR PROJECTED INNOVATIVE) TECHNICAL COMMUNICATION CAPABILITY GAPS.
• BROADENING OF THE CURRENT COMMUNICATION REQUIREMENT BASED ON THE SPECIFIC OPERATING ENVIRONMENT (E.G., LOW DENSITY OPERATIONS).
THE WORK UNDER THIS TASK ORDER INCLUDES DOCUMENTATION, IDENTIFICATION, ENGINEERING, DATA ANALYSIS, DEMONSTRATION SUPPORT, SYSTEMS AND ARCHITECTURE OF SERVICES REQUIRED TO SUPPORT BVLOS FLIGHT OPERATIONS. IN ADDITION, IT MUST COVER DEVELOPMENT OF USE CASES AND SCENARIOS; IDENTIFICATION AND EVALUATION OF SERVICE EXCHANGE ARCHITECTURES; LIVE FLIGHT EVALUATIONS CENTERING ON OPERATIONAL IMPLICATIONS; POTENTIAL REQUIREMENTS ASSOCIATED WITH COMMUNICATIONS AND IDENTIFICATION OF PERFORMANCE STANDARDS AND SECURITY REQUIREMENTS ASSOCIATED WITH COMMUNICATIONS."

prime_award_base_transaction_description: TO 693KA8-24-F-00072_TORFP 2356_ CROSSCUTTING OPERATIONAL RESEARCH AND TECHNICAL EXPLORATION FOR XTM (CORTEX)
subaward_description: THE SCOPE OF THIS TASK ORDER INCLUDES PROVIDING A VARIETY OF SYSTEMS ENGINEERING, OPERATIONAL EVALUATION, AND CONCEPT DEVELOPMENT SUPPORT FOR THE FAA’S EFFORTS TOWARDS THE SAFE AND EFFICIENT INTEGRATION OF NEW TYPES OF OPERATIONS. THIS WORK INCLUDES ASSESSING ONGOING CROSS-DOMAIN ACTIVITIES AND THEIR IMPACTS ON XTM CONCEPTS. TO ACCOMPLISH THIS, THE TEAM WILL CONDUCT OPERATIONAL ANALYSIS AND TECHNICAL ACTIVITIES THAT SUPPORT THE AGENCY’S DECISION-MAKING AND ACQUISITIONS MANAGEMENT PROCESSES THROUGH STAKEHOLDER OUTREACH, LITERATURE REVIEW, IDENTIFICATION OF USE CASES, DEVELOPMENT OF PROTOTYPES, AND OPERATIONAL EVALUATION OF PROTOTYPE SYSTEMS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: BIOMECHANICS CRASH TEST DATABASE
subawardee_business_types: FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,BUSINESS OR ORGANIZATION,LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY
subaward_description: THE NHTSA HAS RECENTLY MODERNIZED ITS CRASH TEST DATABASE AND IS NOW HOSTING IT ON AMAZON WEB SERVICES (AWS). AS PART OF THIS MODERNIZATION, API ENDPOINTS HAVE BEEN DEVELOPED FOR ACCESSING THE DATA. THE OVERARCHING GOAL OF THE NEW CRASH TEST DATABASE SIGNAL ANALYSIS TOOLS (RFP: 693JJ923R000183) PROGRAM IS TO DEVELOP A WEB APPLICATION VERSION OF THE NHTSA VEHICLE SAFETY RESEARCH SIGNAL ANALYSIS TOOL TO MOVE AWAY FROM THE EXISTING WINDOWS-BASED PROGRAM AND TOWARDS A TOOLSET ACCESSIBLE THROUGH A WEB BROWSER. ELEMANCE WILL WORK CLOSELY WITH WAKE FOREST UNIVERSITY HEALTH SCIENCES (WFUHS) TO SUPPORT THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE NEW SIGNAL ANALYSIS TOOL WEB APPLICATION. THE ALLOCATION OF EFFORT FOR EACH TASK IN THE RFP HAS BEEN OUTLINED IN THE FULL PROPOSAL PREPARED BY WFUHS AND ELEMANCE. INITIALLY, ELEMANCE WILL ASSIST WFUHS IN DEVELOPING A TASK IMPLEMENTATION PLAN (C.5.2). THE GOAL OF THE TASK IMPLEMENTATION PLAN IS TO DETAIL THE SCHEDULE, TECHNICAL APPROACH, CODE REVIEW, AND DOCUMENTATION STRATEGY FOR THE SIGNAL ANALYSIS TOOL. ONCE THE DRAFT PLAN HAS BEEN APPROVED BY NHTSA, THE PROJECT TEAM WILL PROCEED WITH TOOL DEVELOPMENT (C.5.3). THE TEAM OF ENGINEERS AT ELEMANCE DEDICATED TO SUPPORTING THIS PROGRAM HAVE EXPERIENCE IN EACH COMPONENT OF THE DESIGN PROCESS REQUIRED TO MAKE THE SIGNAL ANALYSIS WEB APPLICATION A SUCCESS, INCLUDING FRONT END USER INTERFACE DEVELOPMENT, DATABASE AND API ABSTRACTION, FUNCTIONAL AND OBJECT-ORIENTED PROGRAMMING FOR SIGNAL ANALYSIS, AND EXPERIENCE IN CALCULATING AND VISUALIZING THE METRICS REQUIRED BY THE DELIVERED TOOL. ELEMANCE WILL ASSIST WFUHS IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF FRONT-END INTERFACES FOR INTERACTING WITH AND VISUALIZING SIGNAL DATA, BACK-END INFRASTRUCTURE FOR INTERACTING WITH THE DATABASE APIS, AND FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING FOR CALCULATIONS PERFORMED ON SIGNAL DATA OBTAINED FROM THE DATABASE. IN THE EVENT THAT OPTIONAL TASK C.5.4 IS EXECUTED, ELEMANCE WILL ALSO SUPPORT WFUHS ENGINEERS IN THE EXPANSION OF THE SIGNAL ANALYSIS TOOLS TO INCLUDE THE FEATURES OUTLINED IN THE RFP. ELEMANCE WILL SUPPORT THIS EFFORT BY PROVIDING OBJECTORIENTED PROGRAMMING AND CONTRIBUTING TO THE FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING REQUIRED TO INTEGRATE THE ADDITIONAL FEATURES REQUESTED BY NHTSA. ELEMANCE HAS ALSO PUT TOGETHER A TEAM OF ENGINEERS CAPABLE OF SUPPORTING AN ADDITIONAL OPTIONAL TASK (C.5.5) THAT, IF EXECUTED, WILL FOCUS ON DEVELOPING ADDITIONAL FEATURES DESIRED OR REQUESTED BY NHTSA. WHILE NO DELIVERABLES FOR THIS OPTIONAL TASK ARE OUTLINED IN THE RFP, THE ALLOCATION OF EFFORT FOR THE ELEMANCE PROJECT TEAM HAS BEEN COMMITTED WITH PERCENTAGES COMMENSURATE WITH THE OTHER TASKS WITHIN THE RFP

subawardee_business_types: FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION,LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY,MANUFACTURER OF GOODS
subaward_description:
THE PRIMARY OBJECTIVE OF THE SSDI-II CONTRACT IS TECHNICAL
REFRESH OF SECURITY SYSTEMS INSTALLED AT FACILITIES ACROSS THE US.
TECHNICAL REFRESH OF SECURITY SYSTEMS INCLUDES THE ONE-FOR-ONE
REPLACEMENT OF EXISTING EQUIPMENT AND RESOLUTION OF OPEN
SECURITY FINDINGS. WHILE ELECTRONIC EQUIPMENT WILL BE REPLACED,
THE CONDUIT AND CABLE INFRASTRUCTURE SHALL BE REUSED AS MUCH AS
POSSIBLE. THE CONTRACT ALSO MAY INCLUDE FULL SECURITY SYSTEM
INSTALLATION AT NEW FACILITIES. WORK IMPLEMENTATION AREAS INCLUDE
PROCUREMENT, INSTALLATION, TESTING, AND WARRANTY SUPPORT.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: TORFP 2354 - UNMANNED AIRCRAFT SYSTEMS (UAS) TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT (UTM) SYSTEMS ENGINEERING
subawardee_business_types: MINORITY-OWNED BUSINESS,SELF-CERTIFIED SMALL DISADVANTAGED BUSINESS,FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION,DOT CERTIFIED DISADVANTAGED BUSINESS ENTERPRISE,NATIVE AMERICAN OWNED,S CORPORATION
subaward_description: THE SCOPE OF THIS TASK ORDER INCLUDES SYSTEMS ENGINEERING SUPPORT TO UAS ACTIVITIES THAT WILL HELP TRANSITION TO AN INFO-CENTRIC NAS. THE INFO-CENTRIC NAS VISION OUTLINES A MOVE TOWARD AN AGILE INFRASTRUCTURE THAT SAFELY AND SEAMLESSLY INTEGRATES AND SUPPORTS DIVERSE OPERATIONS. WHILE MANY UAS OPERATIONS ARE FLYING WITHIN VISUAL LINE OF SIGHT (VLOS), THERE ARE A GROWING NUMBER OF UAS APPLICATIONS THAT WOULD BENEFIT FROM BEYOND VISUAL LINE OF SIGHT (BVLOS) OPERATIONS. AS THE FAA IS SUPPORTING UTM MOVING FORWARD, WE MUST ENSURE INTEROPERABILITY AND EXTENSIBILITY OF THE ECOSYSTEM. THIS INCLUDES INCORPORATING TECHNICAL STANDARDS AND ENGINEERING INFORMATION EXCHANGES INTERFACES THAT WILL SUPPORT EXPANDING OPERATIONS WITHIN THE UTM ECOSYSTEM. LESSONS LEARNED FROM PROTOTYPE DEVELOPMENT, TEST AND DEMONSTRATION ACTIVITIES WILL BE SYSTEMATICALLY INCORPORATED INTO UPDATED DESIGNS TO SAFELY ACCOMMODATE VLOS AND BVLOS UAS OPERATIONS IN LOW-ALTITUDE AIRSPACE.

prime_awardee_parent_name: AMERICAN INSTITUTES FOR RESEARCH IN THE BEHAVIORAL SCIENCES
prime_award_base_transaction_description: PURPOSE: THE PURPOSE OF THIS PROJECT IS TO EXPAND THE AVAILABILITY AND ACCESSIBILITY OF EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES RELATED TO OLDER DRIVER SAFETY FOR HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS (HCP), USING A VARIETY OF FORMATS AND DELIVERY MECHANISMS AND END PRODUCTS. PRO
subaward_description:
1.	CONTRIBUTE CONTENT FOR A PLAN FOR WEB-ENABLED PRESENTATIONS, INCLUDING THE CRITICAL PATH, DECISION POINTS AND DEPENDENCIES, AND RISK IDENTIFICATION/MITIGATION PLANS FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF A CME/CE EFFORT ABOUT OLDER DRIVER SAFETY FOR HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS. CONTENT INCLUDES:
1.	A PLAN FOR EACH WEB-ENABLED PRESENTATION, INCLUDING A TIMELINE AND REPORT ARTICULATING THE VARIOUS STAGES AND ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN, TO ENSURE NHTSA IS FULLY ENGAGED IN THE PLANNING, DEVELOPMENT, CLEARANCE AND OVERSIGHT OF THE ACTIVITY.
2.	PLAN TO ADDRESS TOPICS SUCH AS HOW TO COUNSEL A PATIENT WHEN CONCERNED ABOUT THEIR DRIVING, HOW FUNCTIONAL DEFICITS MAY PRESENT THEMSELVES AS DRIVING DIFFICULTIES, HOW HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS CAN MAKE REFERRALS WITHOUT VIOLATING PATIENT PRIVACY, THE ROLE OF MEDICAL ETHICS IN ADDRESSING SAFE DRIVING, AS WELL AS OTHER TOPICS SUGGESTED BY THE CONTRACTOR OR SUBCONTRACTOR AND APPROVED BY THE COR(TO).
3.	ADDRESS ANY TOPICS THE CONTRACTOR OR COR (TO) IDENTIFIES AS RELEVANT BASED ON AGENCY PRIORITIES, EMERGING ISSUES, OR CHANGES IN HEALTH CARE DELIVERY OPTIONS THAT WARRANT DIFFERENT OPPORTUNITIES OR CONTENT WORTH CONSIDERING.
4.	NEW AND INNOVATIVE TOPICS, COST EFFECTIVE APPROACHES, NOT PREVIOUSLY CONSIDERED, THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD OF PERFORMANCE. THE PLAN CONTENT SHALL INCLUDE STEPS TO WIDELY DISTRIBUTE AND ATTRACT HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS TO PARTICIPATE IN THE WEB-BASED PRESENTATIONS BY ADDING CME/CE CREDIT FOR PARTICIPATION AND TO ASSESS POST ACTIVITY KNOWLEDGE THROUGH TESTING.

subawardee_business_types: MINORITY-OWNED BUSINESS,SELF-CERTIFIED SMALL DISADVANTAGED BUSINESS,FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION,ASIAN-PACIFIC AMERICAN OWNED,LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY
subaward_description: THE SCOPE OF THIS NEW TASK ORDER INCLUDES PERFORMING CONCEPT ANALYSIS, SYSTEMS ENGINEERING ACTIVITIES, CONCEPT VALIDATION AND DEMONSTRATION ACTIVITIES NECESSARY TO DECOMPOSE AND TRANSITION NAS SYSTEMS BOTH CURRENT AND FUTURE PLANNED TO ADOPT AUTOMATION EVOLUTION STRATEGY AND ALIGN WITH ICN OBJECTIVES. THE TECHNICAL ANALYSIS WILL BE CONDUCTED BY EVALUATING OPERATIONAL NEEDS, FUNCTIONAL DECOMPOSITION, DEFINING, AND VALIDATING OPERATIONAL CONCEPTS AS NEEDED, DEVELOPING REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENTS, TRANSITION PATHS, BEST PRACTICES GUIDES/CHECKLISTS AND ENGINEERING ARTIFACTS (E.G., USE CASES, OPERATIONAL VIEW DIAGRAMS) TO SUPPORT THE TRANSITION OF NAS SYSTEMS TO ADOPT SERVICES-BASED ARCHITECTURE AND ALIGN WITH AUTOMATION EVOLUTION STRATEGY. IN ADDITION, THE TASK ORDER ALSO INCLUDES SYSTEMS ENGINEERING, SECURITY ENGINEERING, PROCESS IMPROVEMENT, VALIDATION ACTIVITIES NECESSARY FOR THE EVOLUTION OF RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT (RD-OE) CLOUD ENVIRONMENT.
